author: WSJ Staff
title: Eight Key Battles in the Spending Bill Fight
text:
WASHINGTON—Government funding expires March 23, giving Congress less than two weeks to finish spending bills for the current fiscal year. A budget deal passed in February set overall funding levels. But that doesn’t mean the spending fights are over.
Lawmakers are now haggling over how that money gets divvied up among government agencies. Here are the main sticking points:
